# AutomateFlow — Tech Stack & Architecture Rules

This document is LOCKED. Do not introduce alternative frameworks, libraries, or
architectural patterns without an explicit instruction from the user that
overrides this file. If a task seems to require something outside this stack,
STOP and ask rather than silently substituting a library.

---

## 1. Monorepo Structure

Tooling: **Turborepo** (npm workspaces under the hood).

```
automateflow/
├── apps/
│   ├── web/                 # Next.js frontend (current campaign-canvas-builder moves here)
│   └── api/                 # NestJS backend
├── packages/
│   ├── shared-types/        # Shared TypeScript types/interfaces (campaign, node, workflow schemas)
│   ├── ui/                  # Shared shadcn/ui component library (if/when needed across apps)
│   └── config/              # Shared eslint/tsconfig/tailwind base configs
├── turbo.json
├── package.json              # root workspace manifest
└── .cursor/rules/
```

Rules:
- Never duplicate types between `apps/web` and `apps/api`. Anything shared
  (Campaign, WorkflowNode, WorkflowEdge, NodeConfig, etc.) lives in
  `packages/shared-types` and is imported by both.
- Never add a new top-level app or package without updating this file.
- Root `package.json` only holds workspace config and dev tooling — no app
  dependencies at root.

