## 2. Frontend — `apps/web`

| Layer | Technology | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Framework | Next.js (App Router) | Public marketing pages (SSR/SEO) + SPA-like client workspace |
| Language | TypeScript, strict mode | No `any` unless justified with a comment |
| Styling | TailwindCSS v4 (CSS-first config) | No `tailwind.config.js`; tokens in `globals.css` via `@theme` |
| Component library | shadcn/ui | Primitives are **Base UI** (`@base-ui/react`), NOT Radix — do not import Radix packages |
| Canvas engine | `@xyflow/react` (React Flow v12) | This IS React Flow — do not install the legacy `reactflow` package |
| Icons | `lucide-react` | |
| State (local) | React `useState`/`useCallback`/Context | Current pattern for canvas/UI state |
| State (global, when needed) | **Zustand** | Already present transitively via React Flow — adopt directly rather than adding Redux |
| Data fetching / server state | **TanStack Query** | Introduce when `apps/api` exists; do not fetch directly in components with raw `fetch` for anything beyond trivial cases |
| Toasts | `sonner` | |
| Testing | Playwright (E2E) | Existing `tests/` spec pattern continues |

Folder convention inside `apps/web/src/`:
```
app/                # routes only — thin, delegate to components/
components/
  <feature>/         # e.g. campaign/, template-builder/
    nodes/
    edges/
  ui/                # shadcn primitives only
lib/                 # pure functions, no React
hooks/               # shared hooks
```
Fix existing drift: Cursor rules currently reference `src/features/campaign-canvas/`
but code lives in `src/components/campaign/` — **`src/components/<feature>/` is
the correct convention going forward**; update any stale rule files.

